  This document lists a couple of features that should be implemented.


------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Daemon
------------------------------------------------------------------------
+ Daemonize (fork) and logging to syslog
+ Use getopt() and read more from config file (e.g. interface)
+ Get nodename from config file so multiple interfaces can be observed
  on one host. (Otherwise we get PK conflicts in DB.)

------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Documentation
------------------------------------------------------------------------
+ Document SQL examples with useful functions, e.g.:
  SELECT FROM_UNIXTIME(unixtime), INET_NTOA(ip), vlan_id, in_bps,
  out_bps FROM count_tbl;
+ Create nice views for the above.
+ Add changelog
+ Update INSTALL with comments abount init.d scripts

------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Python interface
------------------------------------------------------------------------
+ Add a textual interface (get data per IP, get highest users per
  period, etc.)
+ A web interface for the graphs
+ Create means to dump data to CSV and prune the DB of old entries.
+ Replace temp calc95 percentile stuff with new func that does two
  queries (one for in and one for out) so that we have the graph data
  at the same time.
+ Quick writeup of upcoming changes:
  - add 95p lines for all (optional, supply command line option)
  - use command line options to select graph creation and/or textual
    output (summary)
  - move db code into Data.Storage
  - move resultset usage into Data.Result
  - move GraphParameters out of graph.py
  - add proper legend (make human-output optional (otherwise show only
    IN/OUT or something, or custom strings))

------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Packaging
------------------------------------------------------------------------
+ Autoconf
+ Versioning
+ Proper help (manpage?)
+ Adding a "live" graph to the website as "demo".

------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Testing
------------------------------------------------------------------------
